🔍 AI Plagiarism Detector
> Semantic plagiarism detection powered by **Endee Vector Database** and **Sentence Transformers**
---
📌 Project Overview
A modern AI-powered plagiarism detector that goes beyond simple keyword matching. It understands the meaning of text and detects similarity even when content is paraphrased or reworded — something traditional plagiarism tools cannot do.
Key Difference
Feature	Traditional Tools	This Project
Exact word match	✅	✅
Paraphrased text	❌	✅
Synonym detection	❌	✅
AI-powered	❌	✅
---
✨ Key Features
📥 Store original documents in Endee vector database
🔍 Check any text for semantic similarity against stored documents
📊 Similarity score shown as percentage (0% – 100%)
⚠️ Automatic plagiarism verdict with color-coded results
🎯 Adjustable similarity threshold
🖥️ Clean Streamlit web interface
---
🏗️ System Workflow
```
Input Text
    ↓
Sentence Transformer (all-MiniLM-L6-v2)
    ↓
384-dimensional Embedding Vector
    ↓
Endee Vector Database (cosine similarity search)
    ↓
Top-K Similar Documents Retrieved
    ↓
Similarity Score Calculated
    ↓
Plagiarism Verdict Displayed
```
---
🛠️ Tech Stack
Tool	Purpose
Python 3.10+	Core language
Endee	Vector database for storing and searching embeddings
Sentence Transformers	Convert text to semantic embeddings
Streamlit	Web interface
Docker	Running Endee locally
---
🚀 Setup Instructions
Step 1 — Clone this Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/plagiarism-detector.git
cd plagiarism-detector
```
Step 2 — Start Endee Vector Database (Docker required)
```bash
docker run \
  -p 8080:8080 \
  -v ./endee-data:/data \
  --name endee-server \
  endeeio/endee-server:latest
```
Verify it's running by opening http://localhost:8080 in your browser.
Step 3 — Install Python Dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```
Step 4 — Run the App
```bash
streamlit run app.py
```
Open http://localhost:8501 in your browser.
