---
🗄️ How Endee is Used
Endee serves as the core vector database in this project:
Index Creation — A cosine similarity index with 384 dimensions is created in Endee
Upserting — Each document's embedding is stored in Endee with its ID and metadata
Querying — When checking for plagiarism, Endee performs a fast nearest-neighbor search to find the most similar stored documents
```python
# Example: Storing a document in Endee
index.upsert([{
    "id": "doc1",
    "vector": embedding,     # 384-dim float list
    "meta": {"title": "My Document"}
}])

# Example: Searching for similar documents
results = index.query(vector=query_embedding, top_k=5)
```
---
📊 Similarity Score Guide
Score	Verdict
0% – 30%	✅ Original
31% – 60%	⚠️ Partially Similar
61% – 80%	🚨 Likely Plagiarised
81% – 100%	❌ Plagiarised
